description:
&lt;p&gt;Exciting Opportunity for Registered Pharmacy Technicians to join the team!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hello! My name is Alice Smilie, I am the Operational Manager of the John Radcliffe Pharmacy. I am privileged to lead our very hardworking Dispensary team in providing a dispensary service, supplying in-patient, outpatient and discharge medication to Patients of the John Radcliffe Hospital in Oxford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to internal promotions we are looking for Registered Pharmacy Technicians to join our Pharmacy Team on the JR site. This post would be ideal for a recently qualified Pharmacy Technician or a Pharmacy Technician who has worked in community pharmacy and would like the opportunity to gain hospital pharmacy experience. You must have an NVQ level 3 in Pharmacy services or equivalent. The post is full time, however flexible working options would also be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The John Radcliffe Dispensary Team are supported by technology and the robot directly labels medicines before they are released. The duties of a band 4 Technician include dispensing, MDS dispensing, patient counselling and extemporaneous medicine dispensing as well as providing the final check of medicines following successful completion of our Accredited Checking scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The dispensary team is a team of 28 staff ranging from band 2 Assistants through to band 7 Technicians. Many of our band 4 Technicians later go on to become ward based band 5 Technicians or take other roles within the wider Pharmacy team and this role is ideal for gaining that experience to progress further in your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The candidates will be dispensary based, and be required to participate in weekend working on a 1:6 rota basis, early, late duty and bank holiday rotas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 29th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact Alice Smilie, Operational Manager, Charlotte Paddick, Sue Peden, Steve Orton, Senior Technicians, on 01865 221502.&lt;/p&gt;
